Arms displaying eight, serial papular rows with papulae present in similar numbers (20–30 per papular region, but greater in larger specimens). In the largest specimen examined (R= 
14.7 cm
) the papular arm series become extremely irregular especially as they continue onto plates on the disk. Abactinal arm plates round, irregular to scalar in shape. Lobate plates with three to four lobes. Granules round to polygonal, dense, present at identical densities with those on disk. Pedicellariae, identical to those on disk present on nearly every papular region on arm and covering over papular regions. Pedicellariae densities heaviest interradially between “folds” of tegument between disk and arms and along actinolateral edge adjacent to actinal plate series.
